|WKO===========
|YKOThere are two different verions of this command, although both
do basically the same function.  That being to show you your
current level, XP, GP, how much gold you have in the
bank, your HP (and max HP), SP (and max SP), your stats, and your
age.
 
If you type |YKB'score' |YKOyou will get a more abbreviated version of
your score, while typing 'sc' will give you more more detailed,
and if you have it, |KKBa|RKBn|YKBs|GKBi |MKBc|CKBo|BKBlo|WKBr|YKO, version of your score.

|WKBSyntax: |YKBscore |WKOor |YKBsc
